          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhIS7qY-hpQ4itLnjYKBM-CJBtAIK-QzUq1GXZpNT1S74bzg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Judson is a decent place for care but I got to say I'm not a fan of some of the staff. I'm seen at both Gouverneur and Judson but, it feels like 2 totally different places and I don't mean that in a nice way. The heavyset hispanic nurse, is taking my vitals and asking me questions like why you here, but has Airpods on and is in middle of conversation. I say this because she never picks up her phone but after doing my vitals and asking questions goes straight into convo. Like, why am I being asked about myself when you are on the phone. For all I know she talks about me after I leave. I'm sure she does. While we at it, why was she in street clothes? Nearly everyone else has only scrubs but she and another nurse had on jeans.\n\nI never have these problems at Gouverneur. I may wait longer but it's clearly a more professional spot. Think ill be transferring my care there for now on.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xObGMwZHhXWFYzWmxsc1VFSkJPVzlGVUVwWlRWRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x1327e5324f3dbfe9!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlNlc0dxWXV3ZllsUEJBOW9FUEpZTVE%7C%7C?hl=en",
